  "title": "Admin + Accounts Executive / 5 Days work week",
  "description": "<p><strong>Admin + Accounts Executive</strong> <strong>/ 5 Days work week / West (Pioneer)</strong><br />*salary negotiable depending on years of relevant experience*<br /><br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong><br />Monday to Thursday - 8.30am - 6.30pm <br />Friday - 8.30am - 5.30pm<br /><br /><strong>We are looking for administrative staff who are</strong></p><ul><li>Highly organized, responsible, with the ability to meet deadlines and follow through on tasks independently in a fast pace environment</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook); knowledge of POS software is a plus</li><li>Diploma Holder</li><li>Experience in the F&B industry is preferred</li></ul><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p><strong>General Administrative Support</strong></p><ul><li>Handle daily administrative duties, data entry, filing and office correspondence</li><li>Coordinate and liaise with suppliers, customers, tenants and internal teams to address inquiries and provide updates</li></ul><p><u><strong>Record and Documentation</strong></u></p><ul><li>Prepare, verify and input monthly reports (e.g. sales report) into the accounting system</li><li>Perform monthly bank reconciliations for mulitple accounts</li><li>Process monthly GIRO payments and ad-hoc supplier payments</li><li>Issue monthly invoices, including tenant billing, rental charges and cleaning fees</li><li>Maintain well-organized physical and digital filing systems</li></ul><p><u><strong>Ad-Hoc & Operational Support</strong></u></p><ul><li>Prepare tenancy agreements and follow up with tenants for completion</li><li>Manage stock orders when needed</li><li>Track license expiry dates and ensure timely renewal</li><li>Perform ad-hoc administrative tasks as required</li></ul><p><br /><br />*Interested Singaporean/PR please click apply*</p><p>*Only shortlisted candidate will be notified*<br /></p>",
